parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Brake Activation and Vehicle Instability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the brakes can cause the vehicle to jerk or pull to one side, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's brakes engage suddenly and without warning
causing the vehicle to jerk or pull to one side
accompanied by grinding or buzzing noises

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Yaw Sensor and Variable Skid Control System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty yaw sensor can cause the vehicle's stability control system to malfunction, leading to unintended brake activation, loss of control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: and the vehicle may experience unintended brake activation

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed brake booster can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage properly
or the vehicle experiences unintended brake activation
accompanied by grinding or buzzing noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the frame due to rust and corrosion can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
loss of control of the vehicle
and failure of the stabilizer bar.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSC system can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake or lose power, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The VSC and TRAC lights illuminate
and sudden loss of power or braking. The vehicle may pull to one side or jerk violently
